{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848239421,"sessionID":"ses_2873360e8ffe2cGitvBv9LQRIl","part":{"id":"prt_d78cdac20001rOHdT442AUHyuh","messageID":"msg_d78cd9c61001DxQnIFyjsS1yLP","sessionID":"ses_2873360e8ffe2cGitvBv9LQRIl","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_8551f1400d6a40d1bc51857e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** L  \n6: \n7: ## Overview\n8: \n9: Build a Kubernetes reconciler controller in `pkg/workloadmanager` that manages AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter workloads using the generated client-go library.\n10: \n11: ---\n12: \n13: ## Requirements\n14: \n15: ### REQ-001: WorkloadManager Reconciler Structure\n16: \n17: **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with AgentCube CRDs installed  \n18: **WHEN** the WorkloadManager controller starts  \n19: **THEN** it initializes with:\n20: - A typed clientset (`clientset/versioned.Interface`)\n21: - An informer factory (`informers/externalversions.SharedInformerFactory`)\n22: - Listers for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter (`listers/runtime/v1alpha1`)\n23: - Work queue for async reconciliation (`workqueue.RateLimitingInterface`)\n24: \n25: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n26: 1. **Controller initialization**\n27:    - GIVEN a valid `rest.Config`\n28:    - WHEN `NewWorkloadManager(config)` is called\n29:    - THEN a `WorkloadManager` instance is returned with initialized clientset, informers, and work queue\n30: \n31: 2. **Informer registration**\n32:    - GIVEN a WorkloadManager instance\n33:    - WHEN informers are started via `Start(stopCh)`\n34:    - THEN AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers register event handlers (Add/Update/Delete)\n35: \n36: 3. **Lister wiring**\n37:    - GIVEN running informers\n38:    - WHEN a reconciliation cycle begins\n39:    - THEN listers provide cached read access without API server calls\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ### REQ-002: AgentRuntime Reconciliation\n44: \n45: **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime CR is created/updated/deleted  \n46: **WHEN** the informer triggers an event  \n47: **THEN** the reconciler:\n48: - Enqueues the resource key (`namespace/name`) into the work queue\n49: - Processes the resource in the worker goroutine\n50: - Updates `AgentRuntime.status` with current state\n51: \n52: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n53: 1. **Create flow**\n54:    - GIVEN an AgentRuntime CR with `spec.image=volcanoai/agent:latest`\n55:    - WHEN the CR is created\n56:    - THEN status.conditions includes `Ready=False` with reason `Pending`\n57: \n58: 2. **Update flow**\n59:    - GIVEN an existing AgentRuntime with `spec.replicas=1`\n60:    - WHEN updated to `spec.replicas=3`\n61:    - THEN the reconciler scales associated workloads and updates status\n62: \n63: 3. **Delete flow**\n64:    - GIVEN an AgentRuntime CR\n65:    - WHEN the CR is deleted\n66:    - THEN associated resources are cleaned up and finalizer removed\n67: \n68: 4. **Status update**\n69:    - GIVEN successful workload creation\n70:    - WHEN reconciliation completes\n71:    - THEN `status.conditions` includes `Ready=True` with `lastTransitionTime`\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ### REQ-003: CodeInterpreter Reconciliation\n76: \n77: **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter CR lifecycle event  \n78: **WHEN** the informer notifies the controller  \n79: **THEN** the reconciler manages the CodeInterpreter lifecycle with status tracking\n80: \n81: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n82: 1. **Create flow**\n83:    - GIVEN a CodeInterpreter CR with `spec.runtimeRef=<agent-runtime-name>`\n84:    - WHEN the CR is created\n85:    - THEN the reconciler validates `runtimeRef` exists and sets status\n86: \n87: 2. **Runtime not found**\n88:    - GIVEN a CodeInterpreter with `spec.runtimeRef=nonexistent`\n89:    - WHEN reconciliation runs\n90:    - THEN status.conditions includes `Ready=False` with reason `RuntimeNotFound`\n91: \n92: 3. **Successful binding**\n93:    - GIVEN valid runtimeRef and CodeInterpreter\n94:    - WHEN reconciliation succeeds\n95:    - THEN status.phase=`Running` with connection details\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ### REQ-004: Error Handling & Retry\n100: \n101: **GIVEN** a reconciliation failure  \n102: **WHEN** the worker processes a failing resource  \n103: **THEN** the item is requeued with exponential backoff\n104: \n105: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n106: 1. **Transient error**\n107:    - GIVEN a temporary API server error\n108:    - WHEN reconciliation fails\n109:    - THEN the item is requeued with rate-limited delay\n110: \n111: 2. **Permanent error**\n112:    - GIVEN invalid spec (e.g., invalid image format)\n113:    - WHEN reconciliation fails\n114:    - THEN status.conditions records the error and item is NOT requeued indefinitely\n115: \n116: 3. **Retry limit**\n117:    - GIVEN repeated failures (>maxRetries)\n118:    - WHEN the worker processes the item\n119:    - THEN the item is forgotten from the work queue and status marked as `Failed`\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ### REQ-005: Graceful Shutdown\n124: \n125: **GIVEN** the controller receives shutdown signal  \n126: **WHEN** `Shutdown()` is called  \n127: **THEN** it:\n128: - Closes the work queue\n129: - Waits for in-flight reconciliations to complete\n130: - Shuts down the informer factory\n131: \n132: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n133: 1. **Signal handling**\n134:    - GIVEN a running controller\n135:    - WHEN SIGTERM is received\n136:    - THEN `Shutdown()` is invoked within 1 second\n137: \n138: 2. **Work queue drain**\n139:    - GIVEN pending items in work queue\n140:    - WHEN shutdown begins\n141:    - THEN workers complete current items before exiting (or timeout after 30s)\n142: \n143: 3. **Informer shutdown**\n144:    - GIVEN running informers\n145:    - WHEN `Shutdown()` completes\n146:    - THEN informer goroutines are terminated and watch connections closed\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ### REQ-006: Event Recording\n151: \n152: **GIVEN** significant reconciliation events  \n153: **WHEN** status changes occur  \n154: **THEN** Kubernetes events are emitted via `record.EventRecorder`\n155: \n156: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n157: 1. **Normal event**\n158:    - GIVEN successful AgentRuntime creation\n159:    - WHEN reconciliation completes\n160:    - THEN a `Normal` event with reason `AgentRuntimeCreated` is emitted\n161: \n162: 2. **Warning event**\n163:    - GIVEN failed reconciliation due to missing runtime\n164:    - WHEN error is recorded\n165:    - THEN a `Warning` event with reason `RuntimeNotFound` is emitted\n166: \n167: 3. **Event aggregation**\n168:    - GIVEN repeated similar events\n169:    - WHEN events are emitted\n170:    - THEN Kubernetes aggregates them (count increments, `lastTimestamp` updates)\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ### REQ-007: Concurrency Control\n175: \n176: **GIVEN** multiple resources requiring reconciliation  \n177: **WHEN** events arrive concurrently  \n178: **THEN** the controller processes them with controlled parallelism\n179: \n180: **Acceptance Scenarios:**\n181: 1. **Worker pool**\n182:    - GIVEN N resources enqueued simultaneously\n183:    - WHEN workers process them\n184:    - THEN at most `maxConcurrentReconciles` (default=4) run in parallel\n185: \n186: 2. **Resource-level locking**\n187:    - GIVEN the same resource updated twice rapidly\n188:    - WHEN both events enqueue\n189:    - THEN duplicate keys are deduplicated in the work queue\n190: \n191: 3. **No deadlocks**\n192:    - GIVEN concurrent AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter reconciliations\n193:    - WHEN they access shared resources\n194:    - THEN no deadlock or race conditions occur (verified via `go test -race`)\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ## Integration Points\n199: \n200: | Component | Interface | Usage |\n201: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n202: | `clientset.Interface` | `RuntimeV1alpha1()` | Typed CRUD operations |\n203: | `informers.SharedInformerFactory` | `Runtime().V1alpha1()` | Event streaming + caching |\n204: | `listers.AgentRuntimeLister` | `Get()/List()` | Read-only cached access |\n205: | `workqueue.RateLimitingInterface` | `Add()/Get()/Done()` | Async processing with backoff |\n206: | `record.EventRecorder` | `Event()/Eventf()` | Kubernetes event emission |\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ## Dependencies\n211: \n212: - `k8s.io/client-go` v0.34.1\n213: - `k8s.io/apimachinery` v0.34.1\n214: - `k8s.io/utils` (pointer helpers)\n215: - Generated client code: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n\n(End of file - total 215 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L  \n\n## Overview\n\nBuild a Kubernetes reconciler controller in `pkg/workloadmanager` that manages AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter workloads using the generated client-go library.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: WorkloadManager Reconciler Structure\n\n**GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with AgentCube CRDs installed  \n**WHEN** the WorkloadManager controller starts  \n**THEN** it initializes with:\n- A typed clientset (`clientset/versioned.Interface`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775848239409,"end":1775848239418}}}}
